{
  "rules": {
    ".read": false,
    ".write": false,

    "users": {
      "$uid": {
        ".read": "auth != null && (auth.uid === $uid || root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin')",
        ".write": "auth != null && (auth.uid === $uid || root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin')",
        ".validate": "newData.hasChildren(['name', 'email', 'role'])",
        "role": {
          ".write": "auth != null && root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin'"
        },
        "disabled": {
          ".write": "auth != null && root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin'"
        }
      }
    },

    "devices": {
      ".read": "auth != null",
      "$deviceId": {
        ".write": "auth != null && (root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin' || root.child('devices').child($deviceId).child('ownerUid').val() === auth.uid)",
        ".validate": "newData.hasChildren(['secretKey'])"
      }
    },

    "locations": {
      "$deviceId": {
        ".read": "auth != null && (root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin' || root.child('devices').child($deviceId).child('ownerUid').val() === auth.uid)",
        ".write": "auth != null && root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin'"
      }
    },

    "history": {
      "$deviceId": {
        ".read": "auth != null && (root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin' || root.child('devices').child($deviceId).child('ownerUid').val() === auth.uid)",
        ".write": "auth != null && root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin'"
      }
    },

    "alerts": {
      ".read": "auth != null",
      ".indexOn": ["uid", "deviceId", "resolved"],
      "$alertId": {
        ".write": "auth != null && (root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin' || newData.child('uid').val() === auth.uid || data.child('uid').val() === auth.uid)"
      }
    },

    "geofences": {
      ".read": "auth != null",
      "$geofenceId": {
        ".write": "auth != null && (root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('role').val() === 'admin' || newData.child('uid').val() === auth.uid || data.child('uid').val() === auth.uid)"
      }
    }
  }
}

/*
==============================================================================
IMPORTANT NOTES ON THESE RULES
==============================================================================

1. DEVICE WRITES FROM HARDWARE (ESP32):
   The rules above require Firebase Auth (auth != null) for ALL writes,
   including to /locations and /devices. Your ESP32 device CANNOT write
   directly to Realtime Database with these rules using just a "secretKey"
   field, because that field is just data, not an auth mechanism.

   Production-correct architecture (recommended in this build):
   - ESP32 sends HTTPS POST to a Cloud Function endpoint (see API docs).
   - The Cloud Function validates deviceId + secretKey against /devices,
     then writes to /locations and /history using the Admin SDK
     (which bypasses these rules entirely - Admin SDK is exempt from
     Realtime Database Security Rules).
   - This is why locations/history writes above are restricted to "admin"
     role only: only your backend (using Admin SDK service credentials)
     or an admin user should ever write live GPS data.

2. If you want devices to write directly without a Cloud Function
   (NOT recommended for production, but possible for prototyping),
   you would need Firebase Auth Custom Tokens minted per-device, or use
   Firebase Anonymous Auth + relax the locations write rule to check a
   per-device custom claim. The Cloud Function approach is simpler, more
   secure, and is what is documented in the deployment guide.

3. Deploy these rules via Firebase Console > Realtime Database > Rules,
   or via Firebase CLI: `firebase deploy --only database`
==============================================================================
*/
